article.headline: Liberty defeats Norfolk State 17-0
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Josh Woodrum threw for 208 yards and one touchdown and ran for another score to lead Liberty to a 17-0 win over Norfolk State on Saturday. Darrin Peterson, who now has 1,050 career receiving yards, was Woodrum's primary target with four receptions for 69 yards. Liberty (1-1) was limited to just 72 yards rushing, while Norfolk State (0-2) had 159 yards rushing, but totaled just 56 passing yards. The Spartans drove to Liberty's 18 in the first quarter but were stopped when Jacob Hagen forced a fumble that was recovered by Tyrin Holloway. Norfolk State never got past Liberty's 40 for the rest of the game. Woodrum scored on a 7 yard run to give the Flames a 10-0 lead with 6:39 left in the second. Woodrum passed to D.J. Abnar from the 22 for the final score with 5:22 remaining.
